Hudl is looking for an Engagement Data Analyst for its Media team. This is an exciting opportunity to translate data/research into actionable user, audience, content, and business insights.



You Are




Avid social media user and digital/social video content consumer; the first of your friends to know about digital trends and emerging platforms
A constant learner. You strive not just to learn, but to apply what you've learned in your personal and professional life.
Collaborative. You play well with others and have made each team you've worked on better.
An intermediate with SQL. You can write intermediate level SQL queries to manipulate data and power insightful reports
Able to interpret technical analysis. You can understand technical analysis completed by yourself or other analysts and can effectively explain that to a technical audience.
Able to tell stories with data through great data visualization and non-technical wording.
Analytical, analytical, analytical. Making decisions based on instinct raises a red flag for you. You think data is more important than opinions. You love finding patterns in data.

You Will



Work with the media team to




Synthesize large amounts of data from disparate sources into audience insights, content development ideas and marketing recommendations for internal teams & clients
Analyze data from Hudl but also YouTube, Facebook, Snapchat, Instagram and Twitter to develop actionable strategies that increase video viewership, post engagement and channel growth.
Oversee engagement analytics for brand partnership campaigns
Tell digestible stories to internal stakeholders and clients with data; build polished, scalable, insightful decks/spreadsheets that benchmark performance and emphasize recommendations
Manage internal tracking and reporting cadence for critical metrics and KPIs

You will also




Build and run SQL scripts. You will write SQL scripts to pull, aggregate, and transform data for reporting
Build, monitor, and maintain dashboards. You will create data visualizations and build dashboards to make sure Hudlies have the most relevant data and metrics at their fingertips to make more informed decisions.
Tell stories backed by data. You will analyze data and communicate insights that tell a powerful story that will drive stakeholder action.
Learn agile methodologies. You will learn to manage tasks and communication in an agile methodology.
Test. You will work closely with the rest of our Decision Science team to test changes to workflows, reporting, and analytic results and report problems back to the team.
Adjust and update database models. You will implement design changes to data models in Amazon Redshift designed by other data analysts to ensure accurate business reporting.
Manage and prioritize tasks. You will own projects from beginning to end and manage your tasks accordingly to achieve business objectives.
Partner with Stakeholders. You will work directly with consumers of our data projects to vet project ideas, prioritize work, collect feedback, and deliver results.

You Bring




3+ years experience in a highly analytical role
Experience in social media analytics, marketing analytics, audience analytics, consumer insights OR other applicable field at a media brand or marketing team/agency
2+ years experience cleaning and aggregating messy data sets for use in analytics
Proven ability to integrate multiple data sources and translate them into actionable insights that influence business partners

This position is responsible for developing complex algorithms and using advanced modeling techniques (e.g., predictive and prescriptive) to interpret data, extract insights, and help produce data science solutions to enable better decision-making. The role works with large data sets and leverages cutting edge machine learning techniques (e.g., neural networks, time-series forecasting, ensemble learning, and unsupervised learning) to train historical data to predict the validated course of action for pre-specified outcomes. The role requires integration of multiple data sets for feature creation, reduction, and selection to identify the most important unbiased drivers for the prediction. This role partners with the business to understand the business strategy and apply knowledge of statistical, mathematical, and advanced modeling techniques to ask the right questions to derive appropriate outcomes.


This associate collaborates with a cross functional team to develop, deploy, verify product quality, and maintain the predictive model lifecycle to help provide business value for the organization.


Work with business to proactively identify opportunities for advanced analytics utilization
Identify business questions or hypotheses to be analyzed
Identify best statistical or modeling method to utilize
Review prediction and optimization factors
Collaborate with business and IT partners to support the big data and cloud computing strategy
Test and troubleshoot internal advanced analytics tools
Work closely with external vendors on support and maintenance of statistical and data modeling tools
Test and review custom datasets
Support production releases of big data and statistical tools
Review, test and document changes to processes, tools and architecture
Collaborate with analysts and data scientists to use expanded data sets and query techniques
Identify test groups and data sources
Identify control group to minimize bias
Independently conduct ad-hoc data mining activities
Present findings of small to medium-scale advanced analytics analyses to non-technical stakeholders
Work with business to identify and recommend additional test factors and re-test as needed
Participate in continuing education to enhance the level of advanced analytics knowledge and skills
Participate in research, consortiums, seminars, and events to obtain advanced analytics expertise


4 Year College Degree or Equivalent Experience
Graduate Degree Preferred in Computer Science, Information Systems, Data Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Business
3-5 related experience required
Experience with data science techniques such as profiling, a/b testing, ensemble learning, unsupervised learning, deep learning, feature reduction, time-series forecasting, Bayesian Statistics, etc.
Experience in data profiling, data mining, data cleaning, feature engineering and predictive analytics
Understanding of enterprise data warehouses and related data platforms
Hands-on experience with data tools and programming languages including SQL & Python
Must be proficient in developing and tuning Python & Postgres SQL
Experience with data visualization
Hands-on experience with big data & cloud computing
Experience of data models to support advanced/predictive analytics
Must be business-centric, data-oriented, analytically minded and results driven
Demonstrated critical thinking skills to scope and frame problems
Displays excellent judgment to propose effective, business driven solutions
Excellent interpersonal and relationship building skills to effectively educate and coach teammates and business partners
Military education or experience may be considered in lieu of civilian requirements listed
CDMP (Certified Data Management Professional) preferred
CBIP (Certified Business Intelligence Professional) preferred
CAP (Certified Analytics Professional) preferred
DGSP (Data Governance and Stewardship Professional) preferred

Job Description
Description
SAIC is seeking a team member to support the Technology Application, Development and Sustainment (TADS) program under the Air Force Weather (AFW) Systems Program Office. The TADS program supports the development, delivery, and sustainment of an integrated system of weather enterprise hardware and software that provides accurate, consistent, relevant, and timely environmental intelligence to the Department of Defense, other federal agencies, and other countries.


Job Description: Works in cross-functional teams with data at all stages of the analysis lifecycle to derive actionable insight. Translates mission needs into an end-to-end analytical approach to achieve results. Performs the pre-analytics areas of data collection and understanding, data cleansing and integration, and data storage and retrieval. Determines the appropriate analytics based on the data and the desired outcomes, using techniques including feature detection, statistics, data mining, predictive modeling, machine learning, natural language processing, and business intelligence. Interprets the validity of results and communicates the meaning of those results. Has familiarity with data wrangling, analytics, and visualization software and programming languages, including analytics methods for big data. Follows a scientific approach to generate value from data, verifying results at each step.
Qualifications
Typical Education and Experience: Bachelors and five (5) years or more experience; Masters and three (3) years or more experience; PhD and 0 years related experience. In lieu of a degree 4 years of additional experience is required. Secret security clearance required.


The selected candidate will have experiences / skills with the following tools / systems:


Required: Experience with a variety of tools/software used to perform tasks related to data science roles

Desired: Nifi, Kafka, Neo4, Hadoop, Tika, Spark, Scientific Algorithm development, Weather forecasting


Desired Qualifications





Overview
SAIC is a premier technology integrator, solving our nation's most complex modernization and systems engineering challenges across the defense, space, federal civilian, and intelligence markets. Our robust portfolio of offerings includes high-end solutions in systems engineering and integration; enterprise IT, including cloud services; cyber; software; advanced analytics and simulation; and training. We are a team of 23,000 strong driven by mission, united purpose, and inspired by opportunity. Headquartered in Reston, Virginia, SAIC has annual revenues of approximately $6.5 billion. Description
Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services is a state agency that, "Helps People Live Better Lives" every day through our five different divisions; as one of those divisions, Medicaid and Long-Term Care (MLTC), encompasses the Medicaid program, Home and Community Services for Aging and persons with Disabilities and the State unit of aging. Medicaid also provides health care services to eligible elderly and disabled individuals and eligible low-income pregnant women, children and parents. Medicaid provides health care for more than one in every ten Nebraskans.
Examples of Work
As a Statistical Analyst III, you will:
Conduct parts of statistical data analyses
Perform data collection activities
Interpret information and design methodologies for reporting Medicaid analytics
Contribute data interpretation and mapping for data conversion and on methodologies for studies, as expertise allows
Participate on a team in a service driven culture to provide accurate, timely, actionable data
Conduct statistical analysis on Medicaid claims and eligibility data, assimilate multiple data sources into usable analyses for DHHS leadership and stakeholders
Contribute to presentations in a multitude of formats for audiences including agency staff, health industry executives, and public consumers using established mathematical methods and innovative mediums
Collaborate on joint projects with other divisions' analytics teams to serve the State's most vulnerable populations through informed decision making and service provider accountability
Contribute to Division, State and Federal reports according to specifications to appropriate reporting authorities
Qualifications / Requirements
Bachelor's degree in statistics, mathematics, economic/social science research methods, or a related field of quantitative analysis and two years of experience in research and evaluation involving the application of statistical methods and techniques to program, administrative, survey, or demographic data: additional experience in this work can be substituted for the required education on a year for year basis.

OR

Post Bachelor's degree in statistics, mathematics, economic/social science research methods, or a related field of quantitative analysis.



What We Prefer:

Experience with R statistical language, other standard programming languages, Microsoft Office products, other statistical and data analytics tools, health insurance, health-related programs, Nebraska Medicaid programs, survey methodology statistics.


Knowledge, Skills and Abilities
Knowledge of: the principles and procedures of random sampling and probability; the methods and techniques of statistical analysis; resource material concerning statistical data collection methods; employing agency policies, rules, and procedures pertinent to the collection and analysis of statistical data; State and federal laws, policies, and standards governing the programs/projects of the employing agency; the functions of public jurisdictions, business firms, or private organizations effected by the employing agency's mission; the kinds and sources of statistical data pertinent to the employing agency's programs/projects and activities; the demographic characteristics, such as economic, social, industrial, or occupational, of those affected or served by the employing agency; manual and automated methods and protocols for data collection, processing and analysis including personal computers, mainframe terminals, and packaged applications software.



Ability to: communicate in person, by telephone, email, and correspondence, with others to exchange factual information and research analyses, findings, and conclusions; construct tabular and illustrative material such as tables and charts; calculate probabilities; use the capabilities and features of programmable calculators, computers and associated applications software such as word processing, spreadsheets, and databases; set personal and work group priorities and work schedules; interpret and apply State and federal laws and standards, and employing agency rules, policies, and procedures; understand and apply technical narrative material including manuals, handbooks, instructional memoranda, and computer printouts; summarize program/project and administrative data into technical reports; apply statistical methods and techniques to the analysis and interpretation of data; implement statistical studies or evaluation surveys within organizational constraints and available resources.

Description
Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services is a state agency that, "Helps People Live Better Lives" every day through our five different divisions; Public Health is one of those divisions which is responsible for preventative and community health programs and services. The Public Health division is searching for a Vital Statistics Clerk within our vital record team. Click here for more information on the Division of Public Health: http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/public-health.aspx
Examples of Work
The Vital Records Unit is statutorily required to complete registration of all of Nebraska's vital events (Death, Marriage, Birth, and Dissolution). The Vital Statistics Clerks directly assists and processes the received applications for vital records unit. This position is in charge of matching all created certified certificates with the original requests for all births, deaths, and marriages. Examines records requests and other documents furnished by customers to review for accuracy, completeness, and relevance of information and to determine if the criteria of proper purpose established by law for release of records has been met. Makes a final decision whether proper purpose criteria have been met to allow release and issuance of vital records as requested. Produces and releases certified copies of vital records. Operates a variety of office machines and office automation equipment to maintain vital records and to produce certified vital records. Assist with the birth registration process. Handle contacts from birth hospitals and new parents. Assist internal and external customers in regards to received applications for Vital Records at the counter, by regular/expedite mail, and on our website page.
Qualifications / Requirements
Any combination of training and/or experience that will enable the incumbent to possess the required knowledge, skills and abilities. A general qualification guideline for positions in this class experiences in performing office support/clerical functions or records management activities. Preferred Qualifications: Experience in Microsoft word and excel. Bilingual English/Spanish preferred but not required. Fax, email, Outlook. Ten key calculator. Demonstrated experience providing excellent customer service skills in a fast paced and demanding environment.
Knowledge, Skills and Abilities
Ability to: interact with persons from various socio-economic levels with tact, courtesy, and poise; communicate effectively; handle difficult or irate individuals and maintain harmonious relationships; adapt quickly to changes in procedures and conditions and to interruptions which disrupt the workflow; code and record information; compute and total figures involving the use of addition and subtraction; pay attention to detail and ensure accuracy and completeness of records. Ability to: interpret agency policies and guidelines pertinent to office support operations; select, adapt and apply established office support/clerical policies, standards and procedures. Knowledge of: standard office procedures for handling inquiries and requests and processing paper; office record and file keeping methods and equipment including personal computers; and formats used in written business communications. Ability to: interpret agency policies and guidelines pertinent to office support operations; select, adapt and apply established office support/clerical policies, standards and procedures. Team player in a very busy environment.

job_description:
This position is responsible for performing accurate, relevant analysis of information related to the PetIQ’s digital assets. They are responsible for developing a structure and extracting data from multiple applications. They will apply statistical knowledge and data modeling to provide current and high quality information to drive decision making.
Specific responsibilities: Leading the PetIQ digital analytics strategy through
Creating a baseline understanding of the digital user experience performance and build a process to streamline measurement.
Benchmarking marketing metrics against relevant standards and competitors.
Developing scenarios and success criteria for user experience testing.
Leading qualitative and quantitative user-experience research to optimize and inform UX/UI design. Lead UAT testing as needed for new features and functionality.
Working with cross-functional teams to identify and maintain data quality.
Useing data mining and other analytical techniques to identify and suggest optimization opportunities for the digital user experience to inform the roadmap of innovation and improvement.
Leveraging UX qualitative research to look for optimization opportunities
Identifing and exploring relevant third-party data sources to better understand the customer digital experience.
Developing and refining techniques used to measure digital engagement, conversion, and trends for marketing efforts, including campaigns and ongoing programs.
Evaluating the multi-channel impact of marketing activities on the digital experience platforms related to engagement, sales, and ROI.
Managing planned and ad hoc analyses requests.
Ensuring timely delivery of reporting and insights, and build user-friendly answers to basic marketing questions.
Required experience and qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field such as Mathematics, Statistics, MIS, Marketing Research, Decision Sciences, Engineering, Business Analytics, Computer Science or other similar fields.
2-4 years of experience with marketing data.
Experience partnering well with cross-functional teams, being highly collaborative with the ability to build strong relationships.
Strong skills in hypothesis generation, data identification, statistics and testing principles.
Ability to turn insights into business use cases for innovation.
Familiarity with digital marketing platforms, tag management systems and content management systems, common website analytics platforms, mobile sites, and mobile app analytics platforms.
Strong written and verbal communication skills.
Leadership and behavioral competencies
Excellent interpersonal and relationship building skills.
Strong planning and organization skills.
Well-developed project management skills.
Ability to work creatively within a limited budget.
Demonstrated ability to handle multiple priorities and meet tight timelines in a highly competitive marketplace.
What We Offer
 A competitive base salary
 Convenient, west Omaha location
 Generous paid time off package including PTO and holidays
 Medical insurance with low employee premiums
 Voluntary dental insurance
 Voluntary vision insurance
 Company paid and voluntary life insurance
 401K retirement plan with up to a 3% company contribution and instant vesting
 Medical and dependent care flexible savings account

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. We encourage applicants of all ages and experience, as we do not discriminate on the basis of an applicant's age.

job_description:
As a Predictive Modeler Intern, you will assist the members of the Data & Analytics Department on predictive and descriptive analytics projects, including but not limited to predictive models, dashboards, and general data analysis. You will have exposure to and work with executive level managers and employees across the company, and see the results of your work have a tangible impact on the company.


In order to gain the best experience possible, we need this Predictive Modeler Intern to work full time during the summer of 2020 and recommend he/she continue to work part-time into the 2020-2021 school year.
Qualifications:
Bachelor's Degree required, plus must show evidence of enrollment in a graduate program working on a degree preferably in statistics or data science.
Completion of probability and statistics course required.
Experience with some statistical programming.
Work experience that indicates reliability, dependability, and the ability to take direction and work well with others.
Interpersonal skills with the ability to interact effectively with a variety of individuals.
Self-initiative in organizing work and following through with assigned tasks.
Who we are:

Great West Casualty Company provides specialized insurance products unique to the trucking industry and outstanding customer service to the thousands of truck drivers and trucking companies we serve. Over the past 60 years, we have grown to five offices serving insureds in over 40 states. We are now one of America's largest insurers of trucking companies. If your passion is to help others, you value education and continuous improvement, you enjoy participating in community activities, and you want to be valued for your contributions, come be part of our successful team.

Why intern with us?

We offer you a challenging career with a competitive compensation and other benefits including:
A 37.5 hour work week.
$18.00 per hour compensation.
Individualized guidance from a mentor.
The opportunity to serve on committees that work on company and community projects.
Assistance securing affordable housing.
To learn more about Great West and our office locations, please visit our website www.gwccnet.com.


Preference is given to candidates whose commute to our corporate office in South Sioux City, Nebraska, is 50 miles or less.

Great People

Great Internships

Interested in working at Hudl? Awesome. Here's what you need to know.




Our goal is to change the way coaches, athletes and analysts prepare for and stay ahead of the competition. Whether it's with video, stats or a combination of the two, we want our tools to help every step of the way. That's why we're always hiring, and we need the best because a product is only as good as the people behind it.




Hudl is looking for an Engagement Data Analyst for its Media team. This is an exciting opportunity to translate data/research into actionable user, audience, content, and business insights.




You Are
Avid social media user and digital/social video content consumer; the first of your friends to know about digital trends and emerging platforms
A constant learner. You strive not just to learn, but to apply what you've learned in your personal and professional life.
Collaborative. You play well with others and have made each team you've worked on better.
An intermediate with SQL. You can write intermediate level SQL queries to manipulate data and power insightful reports
Able to interpret technical analysis. You can understand technical analysis completed by yourself or other analysts and can effectively explain that to a technical audience.
Able to tell stories with data through great data visualization and non-technical wording.
Analytical, analytical, analytical. Making decisions based on instinct raises a red flag for you. You think data is more important than opinions. You love finding patterns in data.
You Will




Work with the media team to
Synthesize large amounts of data from disparate sources into audience insights, content development ideas and marketing recommendations for internal teams & clients
Analyze data from Hudl but also YouTube, Facebook, Snapchat, Instagram and Twitter to develop actionable strategies that increase video viewership, post engagement and channel growth.
Oversee engagement analytics for brand partnership campaigns
Tell digestible stories to internal stakeholders and clients with data; build polished, scalable, insightful decks/spreadsheets that benchmark performance and emphasize recommendations
Manage internal tracking and reporting cadence for critical metrics and KPIs
You will also
Build and run SQL scripts. You will write SQL scripts to pull, aggregate, and transform data for reporting
Build, monitor, and maintain dashboards. You will create data visualizations and build dashboards to make sure Hudlies have the most relevant data and metrics at their fingertips to make more informed decisions.
Tell stories backed by data. You will analyze data and communicate insights that tell a powerful story that will drive stakeholder action.
Learn agile methodologies. You will learn to manage tasks and communication in an agile methodology.
Test. You will work closely with the rest of our Decision Science team to test changes to workflows, reporting, and analytic results and report problems back to the team.
Adjust and update database models. You will implement design changes to data models in Amazon Redshift designed by other data analysts to ensure accurate business reporting.
Manage and prioritize tasks. You will own projects from beginning to end and manage your tasks accordingly to achieve business objectives.
Partner with Stakeholders. You will work directly with consumers of our data projects to vet project ideas, prioritize work, collect feedback, and deliver results.
You Bring
3+ years experience in a highly analytical role
Experience in social media analytics, marketing analytics, audience analytics, consumer insights OR other applicable field at a media brand or marketing team/agency
2+ years experience cleaning and aggregating messy data sets for use in analytics
Proven ability to integrate multiple data sources and translate them into actionable insights that influence business partners
Diversity at Hudl

Hudl is an equal opportunity employer. We understand the power of a diverse teams, celebrate differences and champion inclusion.
